{"title": "Pike Peril", "content": "Why couldn't Merlin have just turned Arthur into an alligator, instead?\n\nPike are a species of carnivorous freshwater fish found in Europe and North America. As an aggressive species prone to cannibalism, they're often used as a rivergoing threat in animal-centered works. They aren't usually depicted as a threat to humans, but they will often be shown as a Super-Persistent Predator towards smaller animals.\n\nCompare The Catfish (where the fish's size makes it a Worthy Opponent to fishermen), Piranha Problem for the tropical equivalent, and Threatening Shark for saltwater dangers.\n\nSee Blade on a Stick for a differently-dangerous kind of pike (both come from a word meaning \"pointy\").", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PikePeril", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheSwordInTheStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Garulfo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheSwordInTheStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBoxOfDelights", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LittleGreyMen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheOnceAndFutureKing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Redwall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WatershipDown", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TedHughes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Pathfinder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AnimalCrossing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsIVOblivion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheOceanHunter"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperPersistentPredator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCatfish", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorthyOpponent", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PiranhaProblem", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThreateningShark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BladeOnAStick", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/JustForFun/IThoughtItMeant", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperiorSpecies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OffscreenTeleporta